title: For Sale:  IWI Tavor X95 Bullpup Rifle in 5.56 with Timney Trigger & Geissele Trigger Lightening Bow
postcontent: This is a must see!  Loaded with upgrades consisting of the Timney 680 Gen II FCG, Geissele Super Sabre Lightening Trigger Bow, Manticore Gasketed Port Cover, and BCM Muzzle Brake/Compensator (shown in final picture only), this like new rifle is a steal!  You're essentially buying a new X95 that already has the most important upgrades that really make a big difference when shooting at a price that is less than the cost of a stock IWI X95 with sales tax in WA!Please note that I accept cash or credit cards with an extra 3.55% fee. Sorry, but not interested in trades at this time.For sale is a like new IWI Tavor X95 Bullpup rifle in 5.56 NATO and is FDE in color.  The rifle comes in its origional box as new and has only been fired on one occasion in order to test upgraded components that were installed.  All told, this rifle has just under $800 improvements and upgrades, the most significant of which is the Trigger assembly, which has been upgraded to the Timney 680 Gen II Assembly.  The combination of the Timney 680 and the user adjustable Geissele Super Sabre Lightening Bow all but eliminated any overtravel the trigger had, minimized pre-travel, and resulted in a trigger with a crisp and clean breaking trigger with a significantly reduced pull weight and ultimately a trigger that feels very much like a standard 2-stage match or competition trigger that you might find in an M4.  The rifle's trigger pull-weight is currently measuring at just over 3.7 lbs.  A list of the major upgrades that have been added to this X95 rifle and a description of each of them and their function may be found below:Timney 680 IWI Tavor Trigger Assembly Gen II -   Self-contained lightweight 6061 CNC machined aluminum 2-stage trigger.  Wire EDM cut, heat treated, Teflon nickel coated hammer to guarantee lifetime service and functionality. Geissele Super Sabre Lightening Bow Trigger - Precision machined from precipitation hardened 17-4 and replaces the standard trigger that comes in the stock Tavor and X95 rifles.  The trigger bow is flatter and changes the angle at which your finger touches the trigger bow, reducing the pull weight modestly.  The Geissele Lightening Bow Trigger is adjustable via a set screw, which removes "slack" inherent in the trigger mechanism used within these unique bullpup rifles.  By removing this "slack" trigger pull is transformed into feeling much more familiar to that of an M4 match trigger, with a clean and crisp break and user adjustable travel.Manticore Tavor/X95 Gasketed Port Cover - Significantly reduces the amount of gas expelled from the rear of the rifle.  While this is not a significant issue when shooting the rifle normally, it becomes an annoyance when shooting suppressed as gas is discharged from the port, which is positioned very near the shooter's face when firing the rifle.  This gasketed port cover provides the greatest seal of any port cover on the market due to its design and the use of a gasket.Muzzle brake/Compensator - Reduces felt recoil and minimizes muzzle rise improving accuracy and your ability to place follow-on second and third shots directly on top of your first shot.

postcontent: Hello!I am selling .356 (9mm/380 auto), .401 (40 S&W/10mm), and .451/.452 (45 ACP/Colt) bullet tips (boolits), whichever you prefer. Just to emphasize, these are only the bullet TIPS (often called boolits). You can use these to load your own cartidges. Obviously it will also depend on what powder, etc. you use, but that's not hard to figure out if you don't already have a preferred formula.I do have written confirmation from the Program Manager (IOI) at the Firearms Industry Programs Branch here in MO that these are perfectly legal to make and sell without an FFL, so there are no laws being broken here (always a plus).The basic "package", per se, would be simply cast and sold. The eye relief is great and it is very easy to look through at all magnifications. The focus works perfectly and when set properly there is 0 parallax. I've had other scopes where that where the focus didn't remove the parallax, but this one works well. I have the original MOA turret and a custom turret with the windmap set to generic and common trajectory. Very similar to .270 win, .30-06, etc. The yardage has been very close although not perfect. Additional turrets can be purchased from Burris very reasonably, although anymore I prefer the MOA turret. This scope also comes with the Butler Creek caps, sunshade, and the Burris Signature Zee rings seen in the photo. The Signature rings are the best always hold without leaving marks and allowing adjustments within the rings. I also have a set of inserts for the rings so you can decide your own level of adjustment, it is currently set for a 20 MOA slant. This is a fantastic scope and I wouldn't hesitate to buy another for a hunting or or combo rifle. Email or text Kris with any questions.

title: For Trade:  Early SKS
postcontent:
This is a true SKS Ghost gun with a 5 digit serial number and no Arsenal stamp. These carbines were manufactured shortly after the Russian government sold the plans, material and tooling for the SKS rifle to China.
 
The first manufactured carbines were called Soviet-Sino the serial number contained a Russian Cryllic as the first character of the serial number as well as  a Tula star on the left of receiver in line with the serial number.
 
The Ghost was the next batch of carbines manufactured under semi direct Soviet supervision, before adopting the a Arsenal 26 triangle with the 3 Chinese characters denoting a type 56 military grade carbine in the later part of 1956. 
 
Ghost guns have Soviet QC/Proof stamps in several locations on the weapon and stock.
 
This SKS is 100% matching including the stock. No cleaning kit or sling.
 
The bore is bright, with sharp rifling, the action is tight, trigger is crisp.
 
Excellent piece of history. Not exactly pretty, but very interesting a great shooter to add to your collection.
 
The SKS is a robust over built weapon for its caliber. Proven in combat in several conflicts, and will outlast most other carbines in its class.
 
Thanks for looking.
 
Trades:
Glock 19's
Lever/Bolt action rifles
Milsurp Rifles
Anything interesting.
No archery or black powder.
